<div class="page">
<div class="textelement" id="58971184" style="position: absolute; top: 806px; left: 10px; font-size: 22px; color: FFFFFFFF;">On MacOS, OpenGL has been deprecated, and only versions up to 4.0 is supported, which means features like compute<br>shaders cannot be used. And, at some point (knowing Apple), OpenGL will be removed.<br><br>So, to help future-proof Processing, I'm experimenting with a new renderer which uses Google's ANGLE, a<br>backward-compatibility layer which translates OpenGL calls into modern API calls (like Vulkan). In addition,<br>I'm also attempting to use GLFW in place of the deprecated JOGL library, as this is an old dependancy that<br>Processing has been trying to move away from.<br><br>Eventually long-term, Processing will need a new renderer which uses a modern graphics API, like Vulkan or WebGPU.<br>However, this could take a while to complete, so this compatibility layer should help to keep things working in the<br>meantime.</div><div class="textelement" id="25629192" style="position: absolute; top: 657px; left: 15px; font-size: 26px; color: FFFFC64B;">Problem is, OpenGL is an obselete API, which is slowly but surely dying.</div><div class="textelement" id="73543648" style="position: absolute; top: 564px; left: 16px; font-size: 22px; color: FFFFFFFF;"><a href="https://processing.org/">Processing</a> uses OpenGL as part of its P2D/P3D renderer, the most frequently used<br>renderer for rendering graphics using the GPU.</div><div class="textelement" id="58199172" style="position: absolute; top: 718px; left: 14px; font-size: 26px; color: FFFFC64B;">At any time, any platform could sunset support or remove OpenGL *entirely*.<br>This is a problem for Processing's feature.</div><img id="16828876" style="position: absolute; top: 220px; left: 360px; width: 747px; height: 340px;" src="data:image/png;base64," /><div class="textelement" id="18444318" style="position: absolute; top: 1177px; left: 8px; font-size: 22px; color: FFFFFFFF;">Progress so far:<br>- Experimented with own C-to-Java OpenGLES library before settling on using LWJGL's library.<br>- Can open window and clear background with color.<br>- Removed all ANGLE warnings.<br>- Cannot render anything to the screen yet. This is caused by null pointers in essential functions like glDrawElements.</div><div class="textelement" id="11259621" style="position: absolute; top: 1373px; left: 8px; font-size: 22px; color: FFFFFFFF;">TODO:<br>- Fix pointer issue.<br>- GLFW keyboard and mouse input.<br>- ANGLE libraries (libEGL.dll, libGLESv2.dll, vulkan-1.dll) to be exported with sketch in sketch working dir.<br>- Find way to read ANGLE libraries in library dir instead of in the root dir.</div><div class="textelement" id="42361532" style="position: absolute; top: 1566px; left: 8px; font-size: 28px; color: FFCAB9FF;">Github repository: <a href="https://github.com/TeoJT/processing4-ANGLE/tree/ANGLE">https://github.com/TeoJT/processing4-ANGLE/tree/ANGLE</a><br><br><br><br><br><br><br><br><br><br><br><br><br></div>
